  "DESIGN_DESCRIPTIONS": {
    "FRD Classic 170": "A compact single-storey home perfect for first buyers or investors. Three bedrooms, open-plan living flowing to the alfresco, and a functional kitchen. Proven FRD quality at an entry price point.",
    "FRD Ranch 210": "A generous single-storey with four bedrooms, two bathrooms, and double garage. The open-plan living hub connects kitchen, dining and lounge with seamless flow to outdoor entertaining.",
    "FRD Hampton 230": "A smart double-storey with living downstairs and sleeping upstairs. Four bedrooms, double garage, and the signature FRD Hamptons facade. Perfect for families on standard lots.",
    "FRD Estate 280": "FRD's premium double-storey - five bedrooms, three bathrooms, and expansive living across two levels. Multiple living zones, butler's pantry option, and architectural facade.",
    "Hillcrest 18": "A thoughtful single-storey designed for 10m lots. Four bedrooms, two bathrooms, and a seamless flow from kitchen to living to alfresco. Proves you don't need a wide lot to live well.",
    "Southcote 23": "Generous proportions and a smart floorplan. The open-plan hub connects kitchen, dining and living, while four bedrooms are zoned for privacy. Practical everyday living.",
    "Willow 26": "A clever double-storey that delivers space on a narrow lot. Four bedrooms upstairs with the master suite enjoying walk-in robe and ensuite. Open-plan living downstairs flows to alfresco.",
    "Fernbrook 28": "A striking double-storey with five bedrooms and three bathrooms. Downstairs is designed for entertaining - open kitchen, living and dining flowing to the alfresco. Upstairs is a private family retreat.",
    "Marseille": "Everyday moments feel elevated in the Marseille. Soft light, stylish finishes and a thoughtful layout create a warm, welcoming home with open-plan spaces alongside restful corners.",
    "Dublin": "The Dublin delivers generous living with a practical footprint. An expansive open-plan zone anchors the home, with the master suite privately positioned for a true retreat.",
    "Almada 210": "Centred around a light-filled open-plan kitchen, dining and living space that flows effortlessly to the rear alfresco. The master suite is thoughtfully positioned for privacy.",
    "Catalina": "Architecturally considered with a focus on natural light and connection. The Catalina's open-plan living is complemented by distinct zones for rest and retreat. Feels larger than its footprint.",
    "Kirra": "Purpose-built for Queensland's climate and lifestyle. Open-plan living with seamless indoor-outdoor flow, three bedrooms, and a compact yet functional kitchen. Ideal for first buyers.",
    "Ella": "A single-storey family home with four bedrooms, open-plan living, and flexible spaces. The Ella adapts to your lifestyle - from home office to kids' play area.",
    "Glendale": "A family favourite with multiple living zones, four bedrooms, and a gourmet kitchen. The Glendale's flexible floorplan adapts to your lifestyle with room to grow.",
    "Fintona": "A premium double-storey with five bedrooms, three bathrooms, and statement living spaces. Ground floor features a grand open-plan area, while upstairs provides a private family wing."
  },
